main event: A large round disc-shaped object, bright blue and red in color, was observed in the sky over Renton, Washington on September 16, 1965.
interesting points: The object had two smaller objects extending from it, one blue and one red, that were circling around the disc.
The object descended in a curving path to about 25 feet off the ground, and moved to the right as the observer moved to the right.
The object was visible for about 30 seconds and then disappeared, with the observer running inside the house.
Weather conditions at the time included light winds, clear skies, and a visible moon.
No sound was reported from the object, and no interception or other air traffic was noted.
sighted object: a large round disc-shaped object, bright blue and red in color, with two smaller objects circling it
